      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's exactly that. \"consistent with a deliberate signal design.\" i knew i wasn't just making it up. i've noticed that when the pulse hits that peak intensity, everyone on my block seems to just... stop. like they're all zoning out for a second. if this is being broadcast through the grid, it's happening everywhere. if someone actually wanted to use frequency to regulate people's moods or keep them compliant, wouldn't the power grid be the most efficient way to do it?",
